HEADWORD: Sailer
<hw>Sail"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
sailor.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir P. Sidney.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A ship or other vessel; -- with qualifying words
descriptive of speed or manner of sailing; <as>as, a heavy
<ex>sailer</ex>; a fast <ex>sailer</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

